## API Calls

All calls go through service classes in `services/apis/`, never directly from widgets:

```dart
static Future<SomeModel?> doThing(String id) async {
  try {
    final res = await ApiService.get(Api.someEndpoint, pathParams: {'id': id});
    if (res?.data == null) return null;
    return SomeModel.fromJson(res!.data);
  } catch (e) {
    logger.e(e);
    return null;
  }
}
```

## i18n

- All user-visible strings in ARB files — no hardcoded strings in widgets
- Key naming: `camelCase`, descriptive (`addFactUploadFailed` not `error1`)
- Add to both `app_en.arb` and `app_zh.arb` in the same commit

## Checks Before Commit

```bash
dart format .          # must exit clean
flutter analyze        # zero errors
flutter test           # all pass
```
